reviews.text: I grab dinner here regularly. One of my ADHD fixations is green peppers with cheese so I always order a green pepper pizza.  I'm not generally a cheesy breadsticks person, but these are the best I have ever had, with lots of crispy cheese around the sides. I always get them with extra butter and garlic salt.  Their pizza sauce is delicious and thankfully not a sweet marinara.  I don't eat meat so I can't vouch for those, but the pickle pizza is also fantastic. The traditional crust isn't very thick, but I will say I prefer the thin because it is nice and crisp. I would (and have) driven here just for the cheesy breadsticks ü§§ü§§
The pizza is phenomenal! This one had brisket that was so good!! The marinara sauce for the breadsticks comes out piping hot.
Always great food and friendly service. I look forward to dinner here every time I visit Ada (monthly)!

My pizza was taking a little longer than expected to be ready. I walked into the restaurant and I was greeted. Then the manager (Ted) apologized and told me it would be a few more minutes than the estimated time I was originally given. He offered me a free drink while I waited, then about 10 minutes later brought me a gift certificate for my inconvenience‚Ä¶.I didn‚Äôt even complain to begin with. This is how customer service should always be handled. West main has always been a family favorite but I had to write up a review. These guys have great pizza and great staff! If you haven‚Äôt tried them yet at either of their locations, I highly recommend! You won‚Äôt be disappointed.

Great food! Great Service! My grandsons always want to go to West Main Pizza.  They want pizza and garlic cheese squares every time. Even when I ask if they want something different they will tell me "no" West Main has the best pizza and cheese squares. We have never been disappointed with any of the food we have ordered.  Thank you West Main Pizza for the great food and service.

detailedReviews.author: Truth Hurts
detailedReviews.text: The food at this pizza joint is honestly pretty good, but I was really put off by the lack of hygiene. I watched the staff handle money at the counter and then go straight back to making food in the kitchen without washing their hands. It's shocking that basic food safety practices aren't being followed. As much as I enjoyed the taste, I can't overlook such a serious cleanliness issue. Definitely something that needs to be addressed before I consider returning.

detailedReviews.author: David Hammond
detailedReviews.text:
I really enjoyed my visit to West Main Pizza in Ada. I definitely enjoyed this place over the one in Dilworth. We ordered a large meat lovers pizza, with a side salad and two 1919 Root beers. The total was 44 dollars but it was enough for 3 people. The pizza was perfectly cooked and delicious. The side salad was ok, good sized and basically what I expected.
I liked how the 1919 Root Beer was served in a chilled glass mug, hower, it would have been nice if the mugs were larger.
It would also be nice if the silverware was a little more durable.
I will definitely be back.
